comments.content: The type I IFNs (IFN family, IFN, IFN, IFN and IFN) all bind to and signal via the type I IFN receptor complex. The type I receptor consists of two main IFNAR1, IFNAR2c receptor chains and other accessory proteins. The pathway above  (WP585) describes the Type I Interferon signaling pathways and shows both classical IFN signaling via the JAK-STAT pathway (dark lines) and other non-canonical IFN signaling pathways.
This pathway was inferred from Homo sapiens pathway [http://wikipathways.org/instance/WP585_r80201 WP585(80201)]  with a 95.0% conversion rate.
